()API integrations kya hai?
--API Integration ka matlab hai do alag systems ko API ke through connect karna taaki wo automatically
data exchange kar saken.
Example: IAM tool SailPoint ko CRM application Salesforce se connect karna.

()API Integration kya karta hai?
API integration systems ko allow karta hai ki:-
data exchange kare
automation kare
accounts create/update kare
access manage kare
Matlab manual kaam automatic ho jata hai.

Simple Example:-
Company me HR system me new employee add hota hai.
HR System
   ↓
API Integration
   ↓
IAM System
   ↓
Salesforce Account Automatically Create,
Matlab HR me employee add hote hi Salesforce account automatically ban jata hai.

()API Integration me kya use hota hai?
Common cheezein:-
API endpoint
Access token
clientId
clientSecret

6️⃣ Real Operations jo API se hoti hain:-
IAM connector APIs se ye kaam karta hai:-
Create Account
Update Account
Disable Account
Delete Account
Reset Password
Assign Role
Remove Role

1️⃣ Java Code Example (API Call – Create User)

Ye example API request bhej kar user create karta hai.

import java.io.OutputStream;
import java.net.HttpURLConnection;
import java.net.URL;
import java.io.InputStreamReader;
import java.io.BufferedReader;

public class CreateUserAPI {

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        try {

            URL url = new URL("https://api.salesforce.com/users");

            HttpURLConnection conn = (HttpURLConnection) url.openConnection();

            conn.setRequestMethod("POST");

            conn.setRequestProperty("Content-Type", "application/json");

            conn.setDoOutput(true);

            String jsonInput = "{ \"username\":\"rahul\", \"email\":\"rahul@company.com\" }";

            OutputStream os = conn.getOutputStream();

            os.write(jsonInput.getBytes());

            os.flush();

            BufferedReader br = new BufferedReader(
                    new InputStreamReader(conn.getInputStream()));

            String output;

            while ((output = br.readLine()) != null) {

                System.out.println(output);

            }

            conn.disconnect();

        } catch (Exception e) {

            System.out.println(e);

        }

    }

}
3️⃣ Example Request

Program API ko ye data bhejega:

{
 "username":"rahul",
 "email":"rahul@company.com"
}
4️⃣ Example Output

Agar API successful ho:

User created successfully

Agar error ho:

401 Unauthorized
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1️⃣ Kya ye xml aur java-code saath me hote hain?

✔ Haan, real IAM system me dono saath me kaam karte hain, lekin alag-alag files me hote hain.
XML file → configuration
Java code → logic / API call

1️⃣ XML Configuration (Connector)

Ye XML IAM ko batata hai API kaha hai aur kaise connect karna hai.

<Application name="SalesforceConnector" type="WebService">

    <Attributes>
        <Map>
            <entry key="apiUrl" value="https://api.salesforce.com"/>
            <entry key="clientId" value="abc123xyz"/>
            <entry key="clientSecret" value="secret123"/>
        </Map>
    </Attributes>

    <Schemas>
        <Schema name="account" type="account">

            <AttributeDefinition name="username" type="string"/>
            <AttributeDefinition name="email" type="string"/>
            <AttributeDefinition name="department" type="string"/>

        </Schema>
    </Schemas>

</Application>
Ye XML kya karta hai
API URL define karta hai
Authentication define karta hai
Account attributes define karta hai
2️⃣ Java Code (API Call)

Java code actual API request bhejta hai.

import java.net.URL;
import java.net.HttpURLConnection;

public class TestConnection {

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        try {

            URL url = new URL("https://api.salesforce.com");

            HttpURLConnection conn =
                    (HttpURLConnection) url.openConnection();

            conn.setRequestMethod("GET");

            int responseCode = conn.getResponseCode();

            System.out.println("Response Code: " + responseCode);

        }

        catch(Exception e){

            System.out.println(e);

        }

    }

}
Output Example:-
Response Code: 200
Matlab connection successful.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
