Complete Connector XML (GET + POST + PUT + DELETE)
<Application name="SalesforceConnector" type="WebService">

    <!-- Connection Configuration -->
    <Attributes>
        <Map>
            <entry key="apiUrl" value="https://api.salesforce.com"/>
            <entry key="clientId" value="abc123xyz"/>
            <entry key="clientSecret" value="secret123"/>
        </Map>
    </Attributes>

    <!-- Account Schema -->
    <Schemas>

        <Schema name="account" type="account">

            <AttributeDefinition name="id" type="string"/>
            <AttributeDefinition name="username" type="string"/>
            <AttributeDefinition name="email" type="string"/>
            <AttributeDefinition name="department" type="string"/>
            <AttributeDefinition name="status" type="string"/>

        </Schema>

    </Schemas>

    <!-- API Operations -->
    <Operations>

        <!-- 1️⃣ GET Users (Account Aggregation / Test Connection) -->
        <Operation name="GetUsers" method="GET" url="/users">

            <Response>

                <Attribute name="id" path="id"/>
                <Attribute name="username" path="username"/>
                <Attribute name="email" path="email"/>

            </Response>

        </Operation>


        <!-- 2️⃣ POST Create User -->
        <Operation name="CreateUser" method="POST" url="/users">

            <Request>

                <Attribute name="username"/>
                <Attribute name="email"/>
                <Attribute name="department"/>

            </Request>

        </Operation>


        <!-- 3️⃣ PUT Update User -->
        <Operation name="UpdateUser" method="PUT" url="/users/{id}">

            <Request>

                <Attribute name="email"/>
                <Attribute name="department"/>

            </Request>

        </Operation>


        <!-- 4️⃣ DELETE User -->
        <Operation name="DeleteUser" method="DELETE" url="/users/{id}"/>

    </Operations>

</Application>
///////////////*
()1️⃣ <Operations>
<Operations>:-
🔹 Ye container tag hai.
Iske andar saare API operations define hote hain.
Matlab:-
Operations
   ├── GET
   ├── POST
   ├── PUT
   └── DELETE
IAM connector ko yahi se pata chalta hai kaun-kaun si API available hain.
------------------------------------------------------------------
2️⃣ GET Operation (Users Fetch):-
<Operation name="GetUsers" method="GET" url="/users">
Ye line kya karti hai
Part	           Meaning
name="GetUsers":--operation ka naam
method="GET":-----HTTP GET request
url="/users":-----API endpoint

Matlab connector ye API call karega:-
GET https://api.salesforce.com/users
Ye users ka data fetch karta hai.

()<Response>:-
🔹 Ye batata hai API se jo data aayega usko IAM me kaise map karna hai.

()Attribute mapping:-
<Attribute name="id" path="id"/>
Meaning:-
Field	     Explanation
name="id":--IAM attribute
path="id":--API response field

Example API response:-
{
"id":101,
"username":"rahul",
"email":"rahul@company.com"
}

Mapping:-
API id → IAM id
<Attribute name="username" path="username"/>

Meaning:-
API username → IAM username
<Attribute name="email" path="email"/>

Meaning:-
API email → IAM email
-----------------------------------------------
()Actual API call:-
POST https://api.salesforce.com/users
Ye naya user create karta hai.

()<Request>:-
🔹 Ye batata hai IAM application ko kya data bhejega.

()Attributes:-
<Attribute name="username"/>
IAM se ye field API ko bheji jayegi.

Example request:-
username = rahul
<Attribute name="email"/>

Example:-
email = rahul@company.com
<Attribute name="department"/>

Example:-
department = IT

Example full request:-
{
"username":"rahul",
"email":"rahul@company.com",
"department":"IT"
}
---------------------------------------------
()Example API call:-
PUT https://api.salesforce.com/users/101

()Request:-
<Request>
Update ke time sirf updated fields bheje jaate hain.

()<Attribute name="email"/>:-
Example:-
email = newemail@company.com

()<Attribute name="department"/>
Example:-
department = Finance

Example API request:-
{
"email":"newemail@company.com",
"department":"Finance"
}
--------------------------------------------


